{
  "text": "The human NCI-H929, U266 MM cell lines and the osteoblastic Hobit cells (kindly gift by Dr. Riggs, Mayo Clinic, Rochester, MN; ref. [CITATION_1] were cultured for 5, 16, 24, 48, and 72 hours with or without 100 ng/mL hrIL-27. MM cells were then stained with Ki67 mAb and analyzed by flow cytometry. Apoptosis was assessed using AnnexinV/FITC kit (Bender MedSystems). Hobit cell proliferation was evaluated by MTT Cell proliferation assay (Cayman Chemical). In some experiments, BM stromal cells (SC), obtained from BM mononuclear cells of MM patients as previously described [CITATION_2] , were cultured 48 hours in the presence or absence of MM cells from patients (n = 2; BMSC/MM ratio, 1:5) with or without IL-27 (50 ng/mL). Cells were than tested for apoptosis by flow cytometry",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "25953962",
    "[CITATION_2]": "9114725"
